# SharpWallet

Tracks and scores sharp wallets on Polymarket. Identifies consistently
profitable bettors using CLV, calibration, and Bayesian win rate scoring.

## Files — Upload All of These to GitHub

|File                    |What it does                                                                      |
|------------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|`scheduler.py`          |**Main entry point.** Railway runs this. Triggers batch scoring weekly.           |
|`leaderboard_scraper.py`|Pulls top 200 wallets from Polymarket leaderboard, filters noise, scores each one.|
|`wallet_analyzer.py`    |Core scoring engine. Calculates CLV, PnL, calibration per wallet.                 |
|`schema.sql`            |Run once in Supabase SQL Editor to create all database tables.                    |
|`requirements.txt`      |Python dependencies. Railway installs these automatically.                        |
|`Procfile`              |Tells Railway what command to run. Do not edit.                                   |
|`.env.example`          |Template for your environment variables.                                          |

## Setup Order

1. Run `schema.sql` in Supabase SQL Editor
1. Upload all files to GitHub repo
1. Connect GitHub repo to Railway
1. Add environment variables in Railway (see `.env.example`)
1. Railway auto-deploys and starts scoring

## Environment Variables (set in Railway dashboard)

```
SUPABASE_URL            Your Supabase project URL
SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY    Your Supabase service_role key (not anon key)
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN      Your Telegram bot token
TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID        Your Telegram chat ID
RESCORE_INTERVAL_HOURS  How often to re-score (default: 168 = 1 week)
MIN_MARKETS             Minimum markets to consider a wallet (default: 30)
MAX_WALLETS             How many leaderboard wallets to score (default: 200)
```

## What Happens When It Runs

```
Railway starts scheduler.py
    → Fetches top 200 wallets from Polymarket leaderboard
    → Filters out whale-gamblers (high profit, few markets)
    → For each remaining wallet:
        → Pulls all trades from CLOB API
        → Calculates CLV per market
        → Scores by category (sports, politics, crypto...)
        → Saves results to Supabase
    → Sleeps 7 days, then repeats
```

## Scoring Tiers

|Tier             |Criteria                          |
|-----------------|----------------------------------|
|`tier_1_sharp`   |Score ≥ 75, 100+ markets          |
|`tier_2_sharp`   |Score ≥ 60, 50+ markets           |
|`tier_3_emerging`|Score ≥ 45, any sample            |
|`watch`          |15–30 markets, not enough data yet|
|`not_sharp`      |Below scoring thresholds          |

